1) PIN CONNECTIONS
RELAY CONNECTIONS (Active LOW)
Salt Motor Relay -> GPIO5 (D1)
Good Motor Relay -> GPIO4 (D2)
Relay Wiring:
VCC -> 5V (VIN)
GND -> GND
IN1 -> D1
IN2 -> D2
TANK SENSOR CONNECTIONS (LOW = FULL)
Xavier Salt -> GPIO14 (D5)
Baby Salt -> GPIO12 (D6)
Aquaguard Good -> GPIO13 (D7)
Bathroom Good -> GPIO0 (D3)
Sensor Wiring:
One wire -> GND
Other wire -> D5/D6/D7/D3
Using INPUT_PULLUP mode.
------------------------------------------------------------
2) SYSTEM WORKING
Step 1: ESP8266 connects to WiFi and Blynk Cloud.
Step 2: Tank Selection using Dropdown
Salt Tank -> V3 (0 = Xavier, 1 = Baby)
Good Tank -> V8 (0 = Aquaguard, 1 = Bathroom)
Step 3: Motor Control
Salt Motor -> V1
Good Motor -> V2
Motor turns ON only if tank is not full.
Relay is Active LOW:
LOW -> Motor ON
HIGH -> Motor OFF
------------------------------------------------------------
3) GAUGE WORKING
Gauge Pins:
V4 -> Xavier Salt
V5 -> Baby Salt
V6 -> Aquaguard
V7 -> Bathroom
If sensor reads LOW (Full) -> Gauge shows 100%
If sensor reads HIGH (Not Full) -> Gauge shows 0%
Gauge range in Blynk should be set from 0 to 100.
------------------------------------------------------------
4) AUTO CUT-OFF SYSTEM
If selected tank becomes FULL while motor is ON:
- Relay turns OFF
- Button resets to OFF
- Notification event is triggered in Blynk
System Features:
- 2 Motors
- 4 Tanks
- Tank Selection
- Auto Cut-Off
- Gauge Display
- Notification Alerts
